  "sozTitle": "User Agreement",
  "sozLastUpdate": "Last updated: June 2026",
  "sozH1": "1. PARTIES AND ACCEPTANCE",
  "sozP1": "This Terms of Use and Service Agreement (the \"Agreement\") is entered into between Fatih Göktürk (the \"Company\") and the user (the \"User\") who benefits from the end-to-end encrypted temporary data transfer service offered through the SecureVault mobile application and the sifreliveritransferi.com website (the \"Service\"). By starting to use the Service, you are deemed to have accepted all terms of this Agreement in advance.",
  "sozH2": "2. DESCRIPTION AND ARCHITECTURE OF THE SERVICE",
  "sozP2": "SecureVault is a temporary data transfer tool with a client-side zero-knowledge architecture. As part of the Service:\n• Files and texts uploaded by the User are encrypted with the AES-256-GCM algorithm on the User's own device BEFORE being sent to the server.\n• The decryption key is never transmitted to, stored by, or processed by the Company's servers under any circumstances.\n• The Company cannot view, read, modify, or recover the content of the encrypted data hosted on its servers in the event of any data loss.",
  "sozH3": "3. SUBSCRIPTION MODEL AND PAYMENT TERMS",
  "sozP3": "The Service is offered at two different usage levels, Free and Premium:\n• Free Plan: Limited to a maximum file size of 250 MB per transfer and a maximum of 4 uploads per day.\n• Premium Plan (Subscription): Provides a maximum file size of 2 GB per transfer and 20 uploads per day.\n\nPayment Infrastructure: Premium plan memberships and billing are carried out entirely through the Google Play Store (Google LLC) in-app purchase and subscription infrastructure. The Company does not process or store the User's credit card, bank account details, or any direct financial data on its own servers. Subscription fees, renewal periods, and cancellation processes are entirely subject to Google Play Store policies. The User has the right to cancel their subscription at any time through their Google Play account settings.",
  "sozH4": "4. TERMS OF USE AND PROHIBITIONS",
  "sozP4": "Although SecureVault cannot inspect encrypted content due to its architecture, the User undertakes to use the Service for lawful purposes only. Transmitting the following content, or using the Service for such purposes, is strictly prohibited:\n• Content that is contrary to applicable law, constitutes a crime, or facilitates illegal activity\n• Files that infringe copyrights, patents, trade secrets, or other intellectual property rights\n• Malware, viruses, or code intended to harm target systems\n• Personal data or private content obtained without the consent of the individuals concerned\n\nIn response to duly issued requests from lawful authorities, the Company is obligated to share the login access records in its possession (see the Privacy Notice/KVKK) with judicial or administrative authorities. Since the content of encrypted files/texts can never be viewed by the Company due to the architecture of the Service, such content cannot be subject to this sharing obligation.",
  "sozH5": "5. CHANGES TO THE AGREEMENT AND THE SERVICE",
  "sozP5": "The Company may amend the terms of this Agreement or the plan limits due to the Service's technical requirements, changes in Google Play Store policies, or the need to comply with applicable law. Updates that contain material changes adverse to the User will be reasonably notified to Users through the app or the website at least 7 days before they take effect. If the User does not accept the new terms, they have the right to discontinue use of the Service and cancel their subscription through Google Play.",
  "sozH6": "6. SERVICE CHANGES",
  "sozP6": "SecureVault reserves the right to change its terms of service without prior notice.",
  "sozH7": "7. ACCOUNT DELETION",
  "sozP7": "You can delete your account at any time. Deletion permanently removes all of your data.",
  "sozH8": "8. CONTACT",
  "sozP8": "For your questions: no-reply@sifreliveritransferi.com",
  "kvkkTitle": "Privacy Notice (KVKK)",
  "kvkkH1": "1. DATA CONTROLLER",
  "kvkkP1": "Pursuant to Turkish Law No. 6698 on the Protection of Personal Data (\"KVKK\"), Fatih Göktürk (\"SecureVault\" or the \"Company\") processes the limited personal data described below in accordance with the law and the principle of good faith.",
  "kvkkH2": "2. PERSONAL DATA PROCESSED AND TECHNICAL SECURITY",
  "kvkkP2a": "Our system is designed with a zero-knowledge architecture, aiming to keep your personal data to an absolute minimum. Accordingly, the categories of data processed are as follows:",
  "kvkkP2b": "• Username / Account Information — Stored irreversibly hashed with the SHA-256 algorithm; the original text is not kept on the server. Retention period: as long as the account is active; automatically deleted after 90 days of inactivity.\n• Account Password — Stored hashed with the Argon2id cryptographic function; your plaintext password never reaches the server. Retention period: until the account is deleted.\n• IP Address (Session Security) — Kept as a SHA-256 hash in an in-memory database (Redis) for the purpose of concurrent session/IP verification. Retention period: at most 24 hours, after which it is automatically and permanently deleted.\n• Login Access Record (IP + Account + Time) — For the purposes of preventing misuse of the Service, providing deterrence, and enabling disclosure to competent judicial/administrative authorities upon lawful request; your IP address (in plain text), the irreversible hash value of your account, and the login time are kept in a separate security record for each login to your account. Retention period: 90 days (3 months), after which it is automatically and permanently deleted.\n• Recipient's Email Address — Processed instantly, solely at the User's request, to send the download link by email; not stored in the database, destroyed immediately.\n• Subscription and Payment Data — Since payments are made through Google Play, your financial data is not kept by us; only the subscription status verification tokens generated by Google and your membership level are processed. Retention period: for the duration of the subscription and as required by applicable financial obligations.\n• File Content — Although not considered personal data, files uploaded are encrypted on your device before reaching the server; the Company cannot access the content. Retention period: permanently deleted the moment it is downloaded, or within a maximum of 1 hour if not downloaded.",
  "kvkkH3": "3. PURPOSES OF PROCESSING AND LEGAL GROUNDS",
  "kvkkP3": "Your personal data is processed on the following legal grounds pursuant to Article 5/2 of the KVKK:\n• Establishment and Performance of a Contract (Art. 5/2-c): Creation of the user account, provision of the Premium subscription service through Google Play Store integration, and the operation of the file transfer service.\n• Legitimate Interest of the Data Controller (Art. 5/2-f): Processing of IP addresses and login records for the purpose of preventing misuse of the Service, ensuring cyber security (e.g., DDoS attacks, bot access), and providing deterrence.\n• Compliance with a Legal Obligation (Art. 5/2-ç): Sharing the login access records in our possession with competent judicial and administrative authorities upon their lawful request.",
  "kvkkH4": "4. TRANSFER OF PERSONAL DATA AND CROSS-BORDER TRANSFER NOTICE",
  "kvkkP4": "SecureVault carries out its technical operations and encrypted data hosting through the Cloudflare R2 cloud infrastructure. Your encrypted data blocks, together with the limited account data described above (SHA-256 hashes), are transferred abroad because the data center infrastructure is located outside Turkey. In addition, for the purpose of carrying out subscription processes, subscription verification tokens are shared reciprocally with Google Play Store (Google LLC, USA) systems. These transfers are carried out securely on the basis of the User's explicit in-app consent and the standard contractual clauses (SCC) entered into with the relevant service providers, within the scope of Article 9 of the KVKK. Your data is never transferred to local third parties or advertising companies. Upon a duly lawful request from competent judicial/administrative authorities, the login access records described above (Article 2) may be shared with the relevant authorities.",
  "kvkkH5": "5. RIGHTS OF THE DATA SUBJECT AND HOW TO APPLY",
  "kvkkP5": "Pursuant to Article 11 of the KVKK, you have the right to learn whether your personal data is being processed, to request information if it has been processed, and to request its deletion or correction. Since your plaintext data (such as your username) is hashed due to our security architecture, in order to verify your identity you may submit your request directly through the \"Delete My Account\" button within the app, or contact us at destek@sifreliveritransferi.com to exercise your legal rights.",
  "kvkkH6": "6. CONTACT",
  "kvkkP6": "For your questions: no-reply@sifreliveritransferi.com",
  "termsTitle": "Disclaimer",
  "termsHeader": "DISCLAIMER STATEMENT",
  "termsIntro": "By using the SecureVault service, every user is deemed to have accepted the following matters in advance, given the nature and architecture of the system, and to have released the Company from liability in this regard to the fullest extent possible:",
  "terms1Title": "End-to-End Encryption — We Cannot Access the Content",
  "terms1Body": "Your files and texts are encrypted with AES-256-GCM on your own device BEFORE being uploaded to the server. The decryption key is never sent to our servers. Therefore, as the service provider, we cannot view, read, or recover the content of the files you send (zero-knowledge architecture).",
  "terms2Title": "Temporary Transfer Tool — Not Permanent Storage",
  "terms2Body": "SecureVault is NOT a file storage / backup service. Uploaded files are deleted automatically and permanently after only a short time (1 hour by default) or upon the first download, whichever comes first. Always keep the original copy of your files on your own device.",
  "terms3Title": "No Liability for Data Loss",
  "terms3Body": "Because files are deleted automatically by the nature of the service, SecureVault cannot be held responsible for damages arising from a file expiring, failing to download, or being lost for any technical reason. Backing up your important data is entirely your responsibility.",
  "terms4Title": "Third-Party Infrastructure",
  "terms4Body": "Encrypted data is temporarily hosted on the Cloudflare R2 cloud infrastructure. Because the data is encrypted, this provider also cannot see the content. Service outages or policy changes of the infrastructure provider are beyond our control.",
  "terms5Title": "Lawful Use — Responsibility Lies with the User",
  "terms5Body": "SecureVault may only be used for lawful purposes. You are entirely responsible for the legality of the content you send. Because the content is encrypted, it cannot be inspected; therefore, all legal and criminal liability arising from misuse of the service belongs to the sending user.",
  "terms6Title": "Service Provided \"As Is\"",
  "terms6Body": "SecureVault is provided \"as is\" without any warranty. There may be interruptions, delays, or errors in the service. There is no guarantee that the service will operate without interruption or error.",
  "termsFooter": "This text is general information and does not constitute legal advice.",
